# All site-specific labels, topics, links, and integration IDs live in
# `site.config.yaml` at the consumer site's project root. See
# `site.config.example.yaml` in this template for the full schema.
#
# This file documents only the SECRETS — values that must never land
# in a git-committed YAML and are owned by the lord at deploy time.
# Set them in Cloudflare Pages → Settings → Environment variables for
# the project (production AND preview), or in a local `.env` for
# `astro dev`.

# --- Web Push (Cloudflare Worker) ---
# The VAPID private key is a Worker secret, NOT a Pages env var. The
# Worker also needs:
#   VAPID_PUBLIC_KEY   (mirrors the public key in site.config.yaml)
#   VAPID_PRIVATE_KEY  (secret)
#   VAPID_SUBJECT      (e.g. mailto:admin@example.com)
#   PUSH_AUTH_BEARER   (the secret the publisher passes to /api/push/send)
# See workers/push/README.md.

# --- Overlord brain (MongoDB) ---
# Read by skills running in the publisher's sandbox, NEVER by template
# pages. The template doesn't read MONGO_URI directly — operational only.
# MONGO_URI="mongodb://overlord:<pw>@overlord-mongo.example.ts.net:27017/overlord?authSource=admin"

# --- GitHub deploy / publisher gh-config ---
# The publisher's sandbox mounts the gh config from the gateway. No
# explicit GITHUB_TOKEN env var.
